Um die Verarbeitung von Informationen, sei es in Gestalt von Programmen, sei es in Form von Daten, geht es stets in der Informatik. Programme sollen die Informationen, die sie tragen, f{\"{u}}r den Leser deutlich zum Ausdruck bringen, und das in unmissverst{\"{a}}ndlicher Weise. Informationen m{\"{u}}ssen in speichern so abgelegt werde, dass sie wiedergefunden werden, und zwar speicherplatzsparend und zeitsparend. Informationen k{\"{o}}nnen mittels verschiedener Tr{\"{a}}ger ausgetauscht werden, sie k{\"{o}}nnen akustischer oder graphischer Natur sein oder, wie heute meist, lineare Zeichenfolgen.
{\ldots}

Computer science is often referred to as the study of information processing, which is also expressed in the name of our subject by the word "computer science" (German word ``Informatik''). So the concept of information should play an excellent role in this discipline. However, water is so commonplace for a fish that it perceives a lot in the water, but that water is liquid, probably the latest. When Mr. Hackl described the idea of ï¿½this symposium to me and suggested that I should contribute something about my topic, I spontaneously agreed, but the longer I deal with the role of the concept of information in computer science, the more embarrassed I got. Computer science is always concerned with the processing of information, be it in the form of programs or the form of data. Programs are designed to clearly convey their information to the reader in an unmistakable manner. The information must be stored in memories in such a way that it can be found again, saving space and time. Information can be exchanged using different carriers, it can be acoustic or graphic or, as is usually the case today, linear character strings. ...},
